Using vole #teeth to track #habitat changes in the #Arctic? That's one way to do it! One of our recent training participants, @PeterSUngar, just published this #newpaper on molar wear in voles as a proxy for diet & habitat. Check it out: https://t.co/Yk6I4WQn8S https://t.co/FSPLI5xMbH

#SharingSciFri: looking for an effective way to #share your #science? Turns out a game might be the way to go! A #newpaper about an #Arctic #ClimateChage card game was effective in helping students retain the information in the long term - read it here! https://t.co/QC9b116Hl5 https://t.co/66nVn4EFxt

On an @IARPCCollab team meeting about the #Arctic Report Card - @AlaskaWx speaking about interconnectedness & viewing the Arctic as a whole. Daqing Yang et al. have you covered with their #newpaper: https://t.co/M3mk1hQbLr and you can look at some of their #river discharge data here: https://t.co/k4ALBmVJHy https://t.co/aohqmzqlSC

#undergraduate #research #opportunity! Do you have undergrads who would want research experience at @Toolik with @USLTER? Of course you do! Have them apply for @MBLScience's #REU at Toolik for the 2021 field season. More information: https://t.co/6AH3uokkoA

The ultimate example of loving data: #SynthesisScience! Satellite observations of snowfall regimes over the #Greenland Ice Sheet from McIlhattan et al uses 2 @arcticdatactr #datasets: https://t.co/p8cpZZ20LJ (Shupe) & https://t.co/5XNSiJHSKd (Pettersen & Merrelli)! #LoveDataWeek https://t.co/f8Txgi1d2g

As part of #LoveDataWeek, the @ucilib gave a great talk on "Data Sharing 101" on Wednesday. Check out the recording here - because loving your #data IS sharing your data. https://t.co/Q7E8bQOGX3 https://t.co/bE5ND2jkSl

#InternationalWomenInScienceDay is most days at the @arcticdatactr - our co-PI (@aebudden), our two projects data coordinators (@sjeanetteclark/@jmultiflorum), our outreach coordinator (@ArcticDataErin), one of our developers, and most of our Fellows/interns are all women!
"Is it possible to change the traditional view of the #polar researcher?" We need to - changing these views has a real measurable impact. Representation matters. -@PolarPrem
@PolarImpact also shared a mental health resources packet to help out #minorities in #polar research and beyond: https://t.co/aHYcJ2YuRC #MentalHealth #DEI
"@PolarImpact exists because [individual researchers of color] NEED it. Otherwise they'll take their time and talent elsewhere." - @PolarPrem
Happening now! #DEI #Inclusion #Arctic @PolarImpact https://t.co/cwl4UgcXWh

New #data archive alert! The #Arctic Animal Movement Archive provides a source of Arctic-relevant on-animal sensor data and contains animal movement and bio-logging data from the Arctic and Subarctic. More info from @ScienceMagazine: https://t.co/s1MKQqHmU8 #LoveDataWeek https://t.co/Jkk6ic4Kyh

Calling educators who love data - do you need tools to teach about #glaciers? The Open Global Glacier Model has interactive apps, graphics, interactive notebooks, and tutorials for you! #STEMeducation #ArcticEducation #DataEducation https://t.co/6FXPuLHMe8 #LoveDataWeek https://t.co/JNE5hkfjVK

Our PI @metamattj was part of the team that created the latest version of the https://t.co/MaD6qaLknv publishing guidelines, which describe how to publish consistent & @FAIRsharing_org https://t.co/H3y1ZpEVEw markup for datasets. Full record here: https://t.co/IufGPqwxh6

#LoveDataWeek is EVERY week at the @arcticdatactr! One way to really love your data is to make sure you're citing datasets each time you use them. For more info on data citation & why it's important, watch this talk from #AGU20 from our Data Fellow, Maya: https://t.co/cNu5TY0xAI https://t.co/AsiIPm6hrp

It's #LoveDataWeek here at the University of California! There's lots of amazing presentations and webinars going on this week, and we at the Arctic Data Center are excited to have more folks loving their #data. Check out the full lineup here! https://t.co/HSEZQLwSHn https://t.co/YLBawHjUwy
